pitt.search.semanticvectors

Class VectorStoreOrthographical

  • java.lang.Object
    • pitt.search.semanticvectors.VectorStoreOrthographical
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CloseableVectorStore, VectorStore

    public class VectorStoreOrthographical
extends Object
implements VectorStore, CloseableVectorStore
    This class provides methods for retrieving vectors that are computed using the orthographical techniques in NumberRepresentation.

    To save time, vectors are cached by default. Methods exist to disable/enable caching and to clear the cache.

    The serialization currently presumes that the object (in the ObjectVectors) should be serialized as a String.

    See Also:
    ObjectVector

      • enableVectorCache

        public void enableVectorCache(boolean cacheVectors)
        Enable or disable vector caching. Enabled cache speeds up repeated querying of the same vector, but increases memory footprint. Cache can be cleared with clear(). By default the cache is enabled.
        Parameters:
        cacheVectors - true to enable the cache, false otherwise
